        - <span role="byline">REUTERS</span>
    </section>

    <p>Af­firm Hold­ings, whose ma­jor in­vestors in­clude GIC, has agreed to buy Cana­dian buy-now-pay-later (BNPL) firm PayBright for C$340 mil­lion (S$352 mil­lion), as the lend­ing start-up looks to ex­pand out­side the United States.</p>
    <p>The deal marks the first ma­jor sign of con­sol­i­da­tion in the BNPL sec­tor, which is rid­ing on an on­line shop­ping boom ac­cel­er­ated by the Covid-19 pan­demic and is now see­ing in­ten­si­fy­ing com­pe­ti­tion.</p>


